Question: Who is Philippe, Duke of Orléans?
Ground Truth: Philippe, Duke of Orléans (1640–1701) was the younger son of King Louis XIII of France and Anne of Austria, making him the younger brother of King Louis XIV. He was originally styled Duke of Anjou and became Duke of Orléans in 1660. He was also granted other titles such as Duke of Valois, Chartres, and Nemours. At court, he was known simply as 'Monsieur'.
